{"source_key":"sha256-332229adf1c17ec1996e205d0779222f","record_index":10,"record_hash":"sha256:4f3921d3d2d9cafb7148d742397081486f09eef2bf4bcb158d221f22ce1d3f25","timestamp":"2026-05-15T20:23:28.949Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes: use `git commit-tree`.\n\n```bash\nnew_commit=$(git commit-tree <tree-sha> -p <parent-commit-sha> -m \"message\")\n```\n\nThat creates a commit object with exactly that tree and prints its SHA. It does **not** move any branch.\n\nTo point a branch at it:\n\n```bash\ngit update-ref refs/heads/my-branch \"$new_commit\"\n```\n\nRoot commit, no parent:\n\n```bash\ngit commit-tree <tree-sha> -m \"initial\"\n```\n\nCommon tree inputs:\n\n```bash\ngit rev-parse HEAD^{tree}\ngit write-tree\n```\n\nSo the full shape is: tree in, optional parents, message, commit SHA out.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-15T20:23:28.949Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}